name: Eefje Depoortere - Sjokz - [Textual Inversion]
description:
also made a lycoris from the same data if you want a smaller file but you can use both at the same time really, set the lyco strength to like 0.3-0.6 if you're gonna do that: https://civitai.com/models/95316/eefje-depoortere-sjokz-lycoris

i made a lycoris out of sjokz cause i think shes god's gift, and since i had the training images already i made an embedding so you can get a smaller file

the standard file is 4,000 steps and it gives me best results

highly recommend dynamic threshholding: https://github.com/mcmonkeyprojects/sd-dynamic-thresholding

dynamic threshholding was used in the 1st, 3rd and 5th image in the showcase

i added a zip of every 100 steps up to 5,000 steps in case you get better results with others (this is the "training data" zip, it doesnt actually contain any training data)

4000 steps, trigger word is e3fj4h
